<li id="cite_note-fn1-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-fn1_5-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Italian_language" title="Italian language">Italian</a>: <i lang="it">Vesuvio</i><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <span class="IPA nowrap" lang="it-Latn-fonipa"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/Italian" title="Help:IPA/Italian">&#91;veˈzuːvjo&#93;</a></span>; <a href="/wiki/Neapolitan_language" title="Neapolitan language">Neapolitan</a>: <i lang="nap">Vesuvio</i> <span class="IPA nowrap" lang="nap-Latn-fonipa"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/Neapolitan" title="Help:IPA/Neapolitan">&#91;vəˈsuːvjə&#93;</a></span>, also <span title="Neapolitan-language text"><i lang="nap">'a Muntagna</i></span> <span class="IPA nowrap" lang="nap-Latn-fonipa"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/Neapolitan" title="Help:IPA/Neapolitan">&#91;a<span class="wrap"> </span>munˈdaɲɲə&#93;</a></span> ("the Mountain");<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Latin_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Latin language">Latin</a>: <i lang="la">Vesuvius</i><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <span class="IPA nowrap" lang="la-Latn-fonipa"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/Latin" title="Help:IPA/Latin">&#91;wɛˈsʊwi.ʊs&#93;</a></span>, also <span title="Latin-language text"><i lang="la">Vesevius</i></span>, <span title="Latin-language text"><i lang="la">Vesvius</i></span> or <span title="Latin-language text"><i lang="la">Vesbius</i></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-fn2-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-fn2_52-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The dates of the earthquakes and of the eruption are contingent on a final determination of the time of year, but there is no reason to change the relative sequence.</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
